tool.name: GDVSpectra_Likelihood

param.name: in_nc_file
param.dialogReference:
A raw satellite data NetCDF generated by the COG Fetch module. Input NetCDF must have coordinates for x, y and time.

Three or more years worth of satellite imagery is required to run this tool.

param.name: out_likelihood_nc_file
param.dialogReference: The NetCDF file containing the GDV likelihood outputs. This output will always contain x, y, time coordinates and a single "like" variable of likelihood values.

param.name: in_wet_months
param.dialogReference:
The month(s) which best represent the wettest period of the study area region. These months, combined with those from the dry season, are used to generate stability information.

Two or more wet period months recommended to ensure sufficient data is available for analysis.

param.name: in_dry_months
param.dialogReference:
The month(s) which best represent the driest period of the study area region. These months, combined with those from the wet season, are used to generate stability information.

Two or more dry period months recommended to ensure sufficient data is available for analysis.

param.name: in_veg_idx
param.expression: MAVI | NDVI | EVI | SAVI | MSAVI | SLAVI | kNDVI | TCG
param.dialogReference:
The vegetation index in which to best represent vegetation "greenness" for the study area. The following vegetation indices are available:

- NDVI (Normalized Difference Vegetation Index)

- EVI (Enhanced Vegetation Index)

- SAVI (Soil-Adjusted Vegetation Index)

- MSAVI (Modified Soil-Adjusted Vegetation Index)

- SLAVI (Specific Leaf Area Vegetation Index)

- MAVI (Moisture-Adjusted Vegetation Index)

- kNDVI (Non-linear Normalized Vegetation Index)

- TCG (Tasselled Cap Greenness)

The default index is set to MAVI, which performed well in the Pilbara region of Western Australia.

param.name: in_mst_idx
param.dialogReference:
The moisture index in which to represent vegetation moisture within the study area. The following moisture indices are available:

- NDMI (Normalized Difference Moisture Index)

- GVMI (Global Vegetation Moisture Index)

The default index is set to NDMI, which performed well in the Pilbara region of Western Australia.

param.name: in_aggregate
param.dialogReference:
Combine all existing annual GDV likelihood outputs into a single median likelihood image. This is recommended to reduce inter-annual seasonal fluctuation.

If not selected, a NetCDF with each annual individual GDV likelihood result will be output instead.

param.name: in_zscore_pvalue
param.dialogReference:
Vegetation and moisture index outliers across time at every pixel can be removed using a Z-Test. The lower the p-value selected, the more statistically significant (i.e., extreme) an outlier must be before it is removed.

No outlier correction is performed by default (set the drop down value to blank).

param.name: in_stand_qupper
param.dialogReference:
The upper n percentile of the vegetation and moisture index values used during invariant target standardisation and rescaling. Percentile is used as the maximum is prone to severe outliers.

The default value is recommended as it typically produced optimal results.

param.name: in_stand_qlower
param.dialogReference:
The lower n percentile of the vegetation and moisture index values used during invariant target standardisation and rescaling. The percentile is used as the minimum is prone to severe outliers.

The default value is recommended as it typically produces optimal results.

param.name: in_fmask_flags
param.expression: NoData | Valid | Cloud | Shadow | Snow | Water
param.dialogReference:
Pixel classes provided by the DEA Fmask algorithm. The DEA Landsat and Sentinel satellite image products come with a mask band to assist in removing clouds, shadow, nodata, etc. Only selected pixel classes shown here will be used in analysis, whilst all others will be masked out (and later interpolated).

The default values include Valid, Snow and Water classes, and all others are masked out.

param.name: in_max_cloud
param.dialogReference:
The maximum percentage of cloud cover allowed within a satellite image before it is discarded from analysis. A value of 0 will return all satellite data with no registered cloud cover.

As a general rule of thumb, the smaller your study area the lower this value should be. The default value is 10%.

param.name: in_interpolate
param.dialogReference:
If checked, linear interpolation is applied along the time dimension at each pixel of the input satellite image NetCDF so as to fill in missing pixels masked out via the DEA Fmask band.

The default is recommended.

param.name: in_add_result_to_map
param.dialogReference: Whether to visualise the outputs of the tool on the currently active map.

tool.summary:
Generates annual groundwater dependent vegetation (GDV) likelihood layers based on a spatial multicriteria evaluation (SMCE) approach. This approach utilises a time-series of vegetation and moisture indices and the stability of both across seasons to determine "persistently green" vegetation typically characteristic of GDV species. Vegetation, moisture and stability are all weighted and combined via an Analytical Hierarchy Process (AHP), resulting in a single GDV likelihood map for every each year present within an in NetCDF file of Landsat or Sentinel imagery (see COG Fetch tool).

Citation: in preparation.
